# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for pyMETRIC-UAV
#
# Goal: keep source (code, docs, configs, example INPUTS) under version control;
# exclude OS/editor junk, build artifacts, Python caches, and regenerable run
# OUTPUTS. A few lines are commented and marked OPTIONAL — flip them depending
# on whether you want rendered docs / example results tracked.
# =============================================================================

# ---- Tooling / editor config (not for publication) --------------------------
.claude/

# ---- macOS / OS junk --------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
.Rapp.history
*.history

# ---- Python caches / build --------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
*.egg
build/
dist/

# ---- Jupyter ----------------------------------------------------------------
.ipynb_checkpoints/
**/.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ---- Quarto build artifacts -------------------------------------------------
# .quarto/ is a build cache; *_files/ are Quarto's per-document support assets.
docs/.quarto/
/.quarto/
docs/*_files/

# ---- Conda / virtualenv (if a user makes one inside the project) ------------
.conda/
.venv/
env/
venv/

# ---- Large source imagery (exceeds GitHub limits) ---------------------------
# The full-resolution multiband image (~2.5 GB) and the resampled copy (~91 MB)
# are too large for GitHub (100 MB/file limit). The demo runs on the small
# clipped image (example_image_clipped.tif, ~14 MB), which IS tracked, and is
# the file referenced by Fruita_Example/config.txt. Ignore everything else.
Batch_Data/*/example_image.tif
Batch_Data/*/example_image_resampled.tif
Batch_Data/*/*.tif.aux.xml
# Belt-and-suspenders: ignore any tracked file over GitHub's hard limit is not
# something .gitignore can do by size; if you add other large rasters, list them
# here or use Git LFS.

# ---- Regenerable model run OUTPUTS ------------------------------------------
# The model writes results into each dataset's Output/ folder. These are
# reproducible by re-running the notebook, and are bulky (multi-MB rasters).
# The small clipped INPUT image and the polygon files ARE tracked — a new user
# needs them to run the demo.
Batch_Data/*/Output/

# Derived input rasters are regenerated from the multiband image on each run.
# Comment these two lines out if you prefer to ship the derived rasters too.
Batch_Data/*/Input/NDVI.tif
Batch_Data/*/Input/LAI_NDVI.tif
Batch_Data/*/Input/FC.tif
Batch_Data/*/Input/TRAD.tif
Batch_Data/*/Input/*.tif.aux.xml

# ---- Validation harness results (regenerable) -------------------------------
validation/results/

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL — decide per project. Uncomment to EXCLUDE; leave commented to TRACK.
# =============================================================================

# Rendered documentation (regenerable with `quarto render`). The source .qmd,
# .bib, _quarto.yml, and the figures/ are always tracked. Uncomment to keep the
# large rendered PDFs/HTML out of git history.
# docs/*.pdf
# docs/*.html

# Doc-support data written by export_metrics.py (regenerable). Currently TRACKED
# so the document renders without first running the export step.
# docs/_fruita_metrics.json
